article.description: Sam Houston St. 55, Stephen F. Austin 52
article.headline: Sam Houston St. 55, Stephen F. Austin 52
article.linkText: Sam Houston St. 55, Stephen F. Austin 52
article.story: NACOGDOCHES, Texas (AP) -- Ryan Bright finished with a game-high 24 points and 10 rebounds to lead Sam Houston State to a 55-52 win over Stephen F. Austin on Thursday night. Stephen F. Austin led by as many as 13 points in the second half. The Bearkats (12-6, 4-1 Southland) trailed by 10 points with more than five minutes remaining, but scored the game's final 13 points to win. The Lumberjacks (11-6, 4-1) didn't score over the last 5:41. Bright, who made 9-of-17 field goals, also led Sam Houston State with four steals. The Bearkats forced 22 turnovers and committed 13. Antuane Miller came off the bench to lead the Lumberjacks with 16 points. His seven rebounds were second on the team to Will Johnson's eight boards. Stephen F. Austin shot 17 percent from 3-point range, making 2-of-12.
